    "id": "D3-Q033",
    "question_text": "A CISSP is auditing a new identity provider (IdP) that uses SAML assertions to federate login across partner organizations. The IdP signs SAML assertions with a single long-lived RSA-2048 key stored in a software KeyStore on the IdP server. Which SINGLE improvement would MOST INCREASE the security of the system?",
