        "text": "Reject the protocol on Kerckhoffs' principle and the 'don't roll your own crypto' axiom, because custom protocols are almost always weaker than they appear to their designers, internal testing does not substitute for public cryptanalysis, and the cost of a post-deployment break is catastrophic; recommend TLS 1.3 with modern cipher suites"
