        "text": "CASB is valuable for SaaS visibility and control. API mode inspects data already in SaaS via vendor APIs (good for sanctioned apps, bad for real-time control of unsanctioned). Forward proxy mode inspects user traffic en route to SaaS (good for in-line control, requires traffic steering). Reverse proxy mode inspects traffic to known SaaS (requires SaaS-specific support). A mature deployment typically combines API mode for sanctioned apps with forward proxy for broader visibility into unsanctioned SaaS, integrated with ZTNA and SWG in a SASE architecture"
