        "index": 1,
        "text": "Absence of reported incidents could mean either genuinely low incidence (good security, low exposure) or poor detection capability (undetected compromises). The CISSP should investigate by measuring detection coverage against known techniques, checking for near-misses and contained events, comparing dwell time estimates against industry benchmarks, and running red team or breach simulation exercises to test whether the team can actually detect realistic attacks; 'quiet' by itself is not evidence of security"
