        "text": "Without central dependency governance, different teams may use different versions of the same library (including known-vulnerable versions), adopt unmaintained or high-risk packages without evaluation, have no visibility into the organization's aggregate dependency risk, and produce inconsistent SBOM quality. A centralized dependency policy with a curated private registry, minimum version standards, and automated enforcement reduces this risk"
